The Herald Sports Reporter
ZIMBABWE all-rounder Sikandar Raza has left for the Trinidad and Tobago where he is expected to take part in the Caribbean Premier League which recently got the thumbs up from authorities despite the threat of the coronavirus pandemic. Raza, who was picked up by the Trinbago Knight Riders in the competition’s draft on earlier this month, is the only Zimbabwean in the competition. The all-rounder left the country on Tuesday, via Dubai. “Super excited to be on my way for CPL. First part of the journey takes me to Dubai. Can’t wait to finally join the TK Riders family. Please keep me in your prayers,” tweeted Raza.